  sodium: 1340 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince one wedge until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Cut @tomato{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp}(2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add @turmeric{1/4%tsp}(½ tsp for 4); stir to combine.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Toss zucchini, onion wedges, and tomato on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}, ¾ tsp @garlic powder{3/4%tsp}(1¼ tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the garlic powder later.)

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add @peas{4%oz} and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings) to a large #microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover with plastic wrap; microwave until softened, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Mash peas with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until almost smooth.

Add @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, minced onion, @tempura batter{82%g}, @Shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, 1/3 cup water (2/3 cup for 4), and ¼ tsp salt (½ tsp for 4); whisk until combined.

> If mixture is too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Carefully add ½-cup scoops of batter to pan. (You may need to work in batches.) Cook patties until golden brown on the first side, ~{3-4%minutes}; flip and cook ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{} and season with a pinch of salt.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{3%tbsp}, lemon zest, remaining @garlic powder{1/4%tsp}, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings). Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide rice, roasted veggies, and patties between plates. Drizzle patties with garlic lemon sauce and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.